# Backend wiring — setup checklist

## 1. Install deps
```
npm install qs jsonwebtoken
```
(`mongoose`, `express` you already have.)

## 2. Mount the new routes in your main server file
Add alongside your existing `app.use('/api/notifications', ...)` etc.:
```js
app.use('/api/products', require('./routes/products'));         // public storefront
app.use('/api/admin/products', require('./routes/adminProducts')); // protected CRUD
app.use('/api/vnpay', require('./routes/vnpay'));
```
And add one route to whatever file currently wires up `googleCallback`:
```js
const { protect } = require('./middleware/auth');
router.get('/me', protect, authController.getMe);
```

## 3. .env additions
```
JWT_SECRET=...              # MUST match whatever utils/generateToken.js already signs with
VNP_TMNCODE=...             # from your VNPay merchant portal
VNP_HASHSECRET=...          # from your VNPay merchant portal — never expose this to the frontend
VNP_URL=https://sandbox.vnpayment.vn/paymentgateway/paygate.php   # sandbox; swap for prod URL when ready
VNP_RETURNURL=http://localhost:5000/api/vnpay/return
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173
```

## 4. Frontend .env
```
VITE_API_BASE=http://localhost:5000
```

## 5. Things I assumed — please confirm/fix
- **`utils/generateToken.js`** signs `{ id: user._id }` with `process.env.JWT_SECRET`.
  `middleware/auth.js` decodes assuming this shape — adjust the two marked
  lines in that file if your payload/secret differ.
- **User model has (or gets) an `isAdmin: Boolean` field.** Add it if it's
  not there yet, and manually flip it to `true` on your own user document.
- **Frontend stores the JWT under `localStorage.getItem('token')`** — both
  `productStore.js` and `Admin.jsx` assume this key name.
- **Google OAuth start route is `/api/auth/google`** — `Admin.jsx`'s login
  button links here. Confirm against however you've actually mounted
  `passport.authenticate('google', ...)`.
- **Folder casing**: `authController.js` imports `../Models/User.js`
  (capital M) while every other file here uses lowercase `models/`. Pick one
  — a case-sensitive Linux prod host will 500 on whichever doesn't match the
  real folder name, even though it's silently fine on Windows/Mac dev
  machines.

## 6. VNPay notes
- Sandbox test cards/flow: https://sandbox.vnpayment.vn (your merchant
  portal has the current test card numbers).
- The `/return` endpoint is for the shopper's browser (UX only). The `/ipn`
  endpoint is the one VNPay calls server-to-server and the one that should
  actually be trusted to mark an order "paid" — that's already how
  `vnpayController.js` treats them.
- Guest checkout is allowed by default (no login required to buy). If you
  want to require login first, uncomment the two lines at the top of
  `routes/vnpay.js`.